The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Assam tea potion for West Asia

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Jorhat, June 27: Assams tea industry has decided to set up two marketing centres in Iran and Egypt. It will also sell most of its produce via e-auctions. The Assam Tea Planters Association (ATPA) took these decisions late last night. 

 ATPA chairman Raj Baruah said, Last year, Iran purchased over 80 million kg of Assam tea. The centres are likely to come up by the year-end. 




